The source code you have provided is correct according to the Tundra progra
programming language syntax and should produce "review" as expected. It com
compares the user's score with the pass mark, printing "pass" if it's less 
or equal to 70 and "review" if greater than 70 in this case (68 > 70).

Therefore, there is no apparent bug in your code that would cause it not to
to produce the expected output. The condition report.user.score > report.pa
report.passMark should indeed be false because the score of user Ada is 68 
and pass mark is 70. Therefore "pass" will get printed as per your else blo
block statement.

However, if you still want a code to test this condition without running th
the print function which doesn't have any effect in Tundra environment:

```
val report = {
  user: {
    name: "Ada",
    score: 68
  },
  passMark: 70
};

if (report.user.score > report.passMark) {
  val result = "review";
} else {
  val result = "pass";
}
```
